  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Bangladesh: Ensuring the Continuity of Life-Saving Support for the Rohingya Refugees 
Affected by the Fire in March 2021</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this project is to ensure the continuity of life-saving services for the Rohingya refugees affected by the camp fire. This IOM project provides emergency shelter and basic household item packages, 2) clears debris and drainage and provides WASH products (drainage, slabs, risers), 3) reconstructs damaged WASH facilities, installs wells and water points and distributes hygiene items, 4) provides health care services including mental health and 5) reconstructs Women&apos;s and Girls&apos; Safe Spaces and provides dignity kits among other activities The project provides life-saving assistance to approximately 56,600 people, including 15,000 women, 13,000 men, 19,000 children, and 600 people with disabilities.</narrative>
  </description>
